### Health check (db + redis)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/v1/health

### Register (customer + affiliate by default)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/v1/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Test User",
  "email": "test.user@example.com",
  "password": "StrongPass123!",
  "asVendor": false
}

### Register validation failure (weak password)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/v1/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Bad Password User",
  "email": "bad.password@example.com",
  "password": "12345",
  "accountType": "CUSTOMER"
}

### Register (vendor only)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/v1/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Vendor User",
  "email": "vendor.user@example.com",
  "password": "StrongPass123!",
  "accountType": "VENDOR"
}

### Register (customer + vendor)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/v1/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Hybrid User",
  "email": "hybrid.user@example.com",
  "password": "StrongPass123!",
  "accountType": "BOTH"
}

### Login failure (wrong password, generic message)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test.user@example.com",
  "password": "WrongPassword123!"
}

### Login (stores cookies in REST client session)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test.user@example.com",
  "password": "StrongPass123!"
}

### Auth me (requires login cookie)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/v1/auth/me

### Refresh access token (requires refresh cookie)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/v1/auth/refresh

### Referral profile (requires access cookie)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/v1/referral/me

### Wallet profile (requires access cookie)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/v1/wallet

### Vendor protected API (for VENDOR or BOTH user session)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/v1/vendor/ping

### Admin protected API (should be 403 for non-admin)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/v1/admin/ping

### Logout (clears auth + refresh cookies)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/v1/auth/logout

### Me after logout (should return 401)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/v1/auth/me
